---
import Text from "@/components/fundations/elements/Text.astro";
import Wrapper from "@/components/fundations/containers/Wrapper.astro";
---

<section style="background:#faf8f5;" class="py-20 lg:py-24 border-y border-base-100">
  <Wrapper variant="standard">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <!-- Objection callout -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-8 lg:p-10 mb-8 border border-base-200" style="background:#fff;">
        <Text tag="p" variant="displayXS" class="font-display font-bold text-base-950 leading-snug mb-2">
          "Can't I just share my Google link and ask customers to review me?"
        </Text>
      </div>

      <!-- Response -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-5">
        <Text tag="p" variant="textBase" class="text-base-600 leading-relaxed">
          Yes, you can. Most business owners try that.
          Here's what happens: you send the link, a few people click it, one or two leave a review.
          The rest mean to do it later. Later never comes.
        </Text>
        <Text tag="p" variant="textBase" class="text-base-600 leading-relaxed">
          And the one customer who had a bad day? They didn't need a link. They found Google on their own.
        </Text>
        <Text tag="p" variant="textBase" class="font-medium text-base-800 leading-relaxed">
          TapThrive is different in three ways your Google link isn't:
        </Text>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mt-2">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 rounded-xl border border-base-100" style="background:#f0f7f2;">
            <div class="size-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-white text-sm font-bold" style="background:#1a3a2a;">1</div>
            <div>
              <Text tag="p" variant="textBase" class="font-semibold text-base-900">It catches the moment.</Text>
              <Text tag="p" variant="textSM" class="text-base-500 mt-1">
                A tap or scan at the counter captures the feeling while it's still fresh — not hours later over WhatsApp.
              </Text>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 rounded-xl border border-base-100" style="background:#f0f7f2;">
            <div class="size-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-white text-sm font-bold" style="background:#1a3a2a;">2</div>
            <div>
              <Text tag="p" variant="textBase" class="font-semibold text-base-900">It filters before it publishes.</Text>
              <Text tag="p" variant="textSM" class="text-base-500 mt-1">
                Unhappy customers go to your private inbox, not Google. You resolve it. They move on. Your rating stays clean.
              </Text>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 rounded-xl border border-base-100" style="background:#f0f7f2;">
            <div class="size-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-white text-sm font-bold" style="background:#1a3a2a;">3</div>
            <div>
              <Text tag="p" variant="textBase" class="font-semibold text-base-900">It follows up for you.</Text>
              <Text tag="p" variant="textSM" class="text-base-500 mt-1">
                Customers who tapped but didn't review get a friendly WhatsApp nudge within 2 hours — automatically, on your behalf.
              </Text>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Text tag="p" variant="textBase" class="font-semibold text-base-900 mt-4" style="border-left:3px solid #c97d2e; padding-left:1rem;">
          A Google link asks. TapThrive converts.
        </Text>
      </div>

    </div>
  </Wrapper>
</section>
